Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这一章节的《Wolfram 笔记本介绍》
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.50,0:00:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,讲解了一个更合适的表格格式化工具
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.40,0:00:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,就像这里所示的表格
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.00,0:00:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and is specifically about options for setting up details,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.90,0:00:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,例如分割线
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.50,0:00:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,还有交错底色的横行
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.00,0:00:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,还有调整表格中每个单元格外观的工具
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.50,0:00:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们从第一个样例开始
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.90,0:00:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是生成一个表格范例的输入
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.90,0:00:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,执行这个输入，我们得到了一个输出单元
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.60,0:00:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我将把它转换为文本单元
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.65,0:00:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,因为大多数单元格内都是纯文本
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.00,0:00:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这个输入使用了 Grid 内置符号
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.00,0:00:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Grid 内置符号的第一个参数
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.70,0:00:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,是真正被放在表格中的数组
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.50,0:00:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,该数组给出了表头和占位符
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.50,0:00:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这里有六个选项
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.10,0:00:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“背景”(Background) 选项设置表格的背景为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.00,0:00:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,横行交错使用白色和灰色
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我点击表格内部
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.75,0:00:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,然后按下 Ctrl + 回车 以增加更多的行
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.00,0:00:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,交错的背景颜色会在新行中继续延伸
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.70,0:00:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“排列” (Alignment) 选项指定了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.20,0:00:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,每一列中文本的水平对齐方式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.00,0:00:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,和每一行中文本的垂直对齐方式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.70,0:01:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“分割线” (Dividers) 选项用来绘制行与行之间的分割线
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.70,0:01:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是定义表头之下绘制粗分割线的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.00,0:01:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,below the heading is specified.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.50,0:01:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“基本样式” (BaseStyle) 选项
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.60,0:01:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,定义了表格中文字所用的字体
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.90,0:01:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,最后，对象大小 (ItemSize) 选项
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.45,0:01:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,specifies the space to allow for each column,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.40,0:01:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“间隔” (Spacings) 选项定义了列于列之间的空隙大小
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.30,0:01:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,即使被这些选项控制的细节非常多
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它的基本思想依然很简单
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.80,0:01:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,可以发现，许多选项都有着相似的设计
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.50,0:01:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,只需观察他们的效果即可阐明表格中的这些设计\N （译注：需要一定的英语基础）
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.30,0:01:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on a generic table.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.60,0:01:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,这里有一个带有占位符文本的表格
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.15,0:01:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,它的“边框” (Frame) 选项被设置为“全部” (All)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.60,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,以帮助我们清楚的观察行和列
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.00,0:01:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,从“背景” (Background) 选项开始
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.50,0:01:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以设置成单色
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.10,0:01:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,要设置整个网格的背景颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but the general form of the Background option
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.30,0:01:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is a list with three elements
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where the first element
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,specifies the background for columns,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the second element specifies the background for rows
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.90,0:01:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and the third element can be used to specify
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.90,0:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the background for individual elements in the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.00,0:02:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, entering Red, Green, Blue
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.10,0:02:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first element
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.10,0:02:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,causes the first three columns to be red, green and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.75,0:02:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Enclosing colors in a list
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.85,0:02:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,causes those colors to be repeated across the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.00,0:02:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, this gives red for the first column
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and repeated green and blue columns
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.90,0:02:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the rest of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The same structure applies to rows.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.70,0:02:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if that same color specification is the second element
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.50,0:02:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the value of the Background option,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.30,0:02:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the result is a table where the first row is red
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.00,0:02:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the remaining rows alternate between green and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.20,0:02:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The third element in the value of the Background option
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.55,0:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,can be used for specifying the background color
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of individual entries in the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.00,0:02:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, this specifies
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.50,0:02:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the seventh element in the fourth row
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,should have an orange background.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.00,0:02:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Similar principles apply to the Dividers option
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.50,0:02:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the Alignment option and to all of the options
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.50,0:02:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that control specific rows and columns.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.80,0:02:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, this shows a value for the Dividers option
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.90,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives a column divider every third column
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and a row divider above the second row.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.50,0:03:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As with the Background option,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of the Dividers option is a list.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.00,0:03:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The first element of that list specifies column dividers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.20,0:03:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the second element specifies row dividers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.60,0:03:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The dividers can also have styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.30,0:03:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, this specifies that the column dividers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.00,0:03:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,should be repeated thick lines and light gray lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the horizontal divider below the top row
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.70,0:03:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,should be a thick red line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With those general principles in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.80,0:03:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,here again is the first example,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.60,0:03:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,where I will go ahead and fill in some values in the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.20,0:03:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This value of the Background option
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.60,0:03:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,gives the alternating
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.60,0:03:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,white and light gray background for the rows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.60,0:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alignment option specifies
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that items in the first column should be centered horizontally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.20,0:03:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The second column should be aligned on the right,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as is typically done for columns of numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.00,0:03:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and items in the third column are aligned on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.60,0:03:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This value of the Dividers option
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,gives the thick line below the top row
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.50,0:03:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the light gray dividers for all of the rows after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.60,0:04:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The light gray divider becomes part of the background
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.70,0:04:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of the rows except the last one,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,where the divider shows up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.20,0:04:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as a light grey line at the bottom of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The BaseStyle option specifies the default font
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.95,0:04:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to use for all of the items in the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The ItemSize option here
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.00,0:04:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,specifies the width of each column.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.20,0:04:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The first two columns are given as scaled amounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.80,0:04:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which means that they are scaled to a fraction
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.25,0:04:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the formatting width,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.80,0:04:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which is related to the width of the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.60,0:04:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the width of the columns changes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.40,0:04:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with the width of the display,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.70,0:04:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be desirable
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,if the table might be displayed in different windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.80,0:04:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, this value of the Spacings option
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,adds some space between the last two columns.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A good way to learn what these options do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is to try different values for the options
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.90,0:04:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and observe the effect on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, here is a simple Manipulate program
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.35,0:04:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives a control
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for adjusting the space between the last two columns.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than using options for the Grid function,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.65,0:04:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a separate strategy for specifying styles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is to use Item expressions as elements in the table
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:05:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and to specify options within each Item expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, rather than using the Background option
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.30,0:05:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to specify the background color
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.80,0:05:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of a particular entry in the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,another way to get the same effect
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.45,0:05:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make that one element into an Item expression
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.50,0:05:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and to include the Background option
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in that Item expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.30,0:05:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A related feature is using the special symbols
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.30,0:05:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,SpanFromLeft, SpanFromAbove and SpanFromBoth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.80,0:05:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to get table entries that span more than one row
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.50,0:05:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or more than one column.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.10,0:05:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, here is a small table of placeholders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.50,0:05:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Replacing one of those placeholders
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.00,0:05:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the special symbol SpanFromLeft
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.00,0:05:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,causes that entry in the table
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.80,0:05:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to be merged with the entry to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.40,0:05:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There are also symbols called SpanFromAbove
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.45,0:05:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and SpanFromBoth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.60,0:05:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be used to merge entries vertically or in both directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.20,0:05:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The affect actually ends up being the same
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.30,0:05:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as selecting items to be merged
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.40,0:05:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and choosing Make Spanning from the Table/Matrix submenu.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.00,0:05:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As a final example which uses several of these tools,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.80,0:06:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,here is the second of the two tables
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.90,0:06:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that were shown earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.40,0:06:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,together with an input to generate that table.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.40,0:06:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This input again
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.40,0:06:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,uses the Grid function with several options.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.50,0:06:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The ItemSize option specifies columns
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with a width of three,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which means three units called ems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.50,0:06:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,An em is a unit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.80,0:06:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,equal to the point size of the current font.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.80,0:06:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If the ItemSize option is omitted,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.30,0:06:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then the columns are adjusted to the width of the widest item
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.00,0:06:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the column,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.00,0:06:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which here gives a table with columns
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.50,0:06:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that seem a bit too narrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so the ItemSize option is included
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.65,0:06:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to give a table that is not quite so cramped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.90,0:06:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This value of the Frame option draws the divider lines
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.50,0:06:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the frame around the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.50,0:06:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This value of the Alignment option specifies that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,items should be centered both vertically and horizontally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Background option
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,specifies a light gray background for the top row
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.80,0:06:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and alternating orange
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.00,0:06:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and light blue background, for the remaining rows.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Background is used in this table
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.50,0:06:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as a color code for the T and F entries in the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.30,0:06:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Background option happens in this example
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:07:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to give the correct color for all of the entries,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.40,0:07:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,except for one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.40,0:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,where the background is specified in an Item expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that Item expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.00,0:07:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the color for that item would be light blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which doesn't follow the intended color code.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.50,0:07:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This table also includes two SpanFromAbove entries,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.00,0:07:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which are there to generate the two items in the first column
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.80,0:07:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that span more than one row.
